  "prompt": "What are the best Malayalam movies?",
  "response": "Malayalam cinema has produced a wealth of critically acclaimed and popular films over the years. Here are some of the best Malayalam movies that are widely regarded as significant contributions to Indian cinema:\n\n1. **Drishyam (2013)** - Directed by Jeethu Joseph, this thriller revolves around a man's efforts to protect his family after they become involved in a crime.\n\n2. **Kireedam (1989)** - A poignant drama directed by Sibi Malayil, focusing on the life of a young man whose dreams are thwarted by family obligations and societal pressures.\n\n3. **Bharamaram (1987)** - Directed by Satyajit Ray, it is a significant film that explores complex family dynamics and personal struggles.\n\n4. **Manichitrathazhu (1993)** - A psychological horror film directed by Fazil, it's known for its gripping story and strong performances. \n\n5. **G\u67e5\u770b\u66f4\u591a: (2003)** - Directed by Sibi Malayil, a romantic drama that explores the themes of love and longing.\n\n6. **Chidambaram (1985)** - An artistic film by G. Aravindan, it showcases the life of a traditional artist and the intersection of art and life.\n\n7. **Kalyanaraman (2002)** - A comedy-drama directed by Kamal, it tells the story of a man who gets caught up in a series of misunderstandings.\n\n8. **Kochu Kochu Santhoshangal (1999)** - This comedy-drama directed by Sathyan Anthikad showcases the life of a middle-class family and their struggles.\n\n9. **Vinayamoksham (1985)** - A socially relevant film that discusses issues of class and capitalism through the lens of power dynamics.\n\n10. **Sukrutham (1994)** - A poignant drama about friendship and sacrifice, directed by Sibi Malayil.\n\n11. **Bharamaram (1987)** - This classic drama highlights the struggles of the protagonist as he grapples with family and societal expectations.\n\n12. **Chakara (1989)** - A film that reflects the complexities of human relationships and individual aspirations.\n\nThese films represent just a fraction of the rich tapestry of Malayalam cinema, which continues to evolve and produce high-quality content.",
